21:39.530 --> 21:42.030
Sorry to call so late.

21:48.330 --> 21:51.080
Mom, I'm okay.

22:00.340 --> 22:03.470
I'll make sure that you
get the best possible treatment.

22:03.550 --> 22:07.560
-I don't care how much it costs.
-You're going to buy her a new colon?

22:07.640 --> 22:09.310
I will not have
a money discussion.

22:09.390 --> 22:11.730
The gloves are coming off.

22:11.810 --> 22:14.310
Money is the only thing
you can talk about.

22:14.400 --> 22:18.990
Marley needs our love and support.
At least pretend to be here for her.

22:19.070 --> 22:22.120
I don't have to pretend.
That's your department.

22:26.450 --> 22:28.290
I'm so glad we got together.

22:33.540 --> 22:35.380
So what did you tell Rob?

22:36.420 --> 22:37.790
-That I have mono.
-Right.

22:37.880 --> 22:39.380
And I'm working from home.

22:39.460 --> 22:41.840
I don't want anybody
from work knowing.

22:41.920 --> 22:45.930
I got it.
Your butt is your business.

22:46.970 --> 22:48.600
Huh? Huh?

22:48.680 --> 22:51.430
-My Dad flew out this morning.
-Is your Mom happy?

22:51.520 --> 22:53.690
So much so she's celebrating
by moving here.

22:53.770 --> 22:58.150
We must warn the populace.
Marley's Mom is descending.

22:58.230 --> 22:59.980
♪ it could be ten but then again

23:00.070 --> 23:04.570
♪ I can't remember half an hour
since a quarter to four

23:04.650 --> 23:07.580
♪ throw on your clothes,
the second side of Surfer Rosa

23:07.660 --> 23:11.710
♪ and you leave me with my jaw below
Hey hey

23:14.710 --> 23:17.000
♪ just when you think
you're in control

23:17.080 --> 23:19.380
♪ just when you think
you've got a hold

23:19.460 --> 23:21.180
♪ just when you think
you get on a roll

23:21.250 --> 23:23.970
♪ here it goes, here it goes,
here it goes again ♪

23:24.050 --> 23:27.640
-(Radio DJ): I'll take caller 97...
-Get the phone.

23:27.720 --> 23:29.640
-to win a prize in our contest
-What?

23:29.720 --> 23:32.940
-Quick, Marley.
-(DJ): Code 9797.

23:33.020 --> 23:35.990
-Go on! 9797.
-I got it.

23:36.060 --> 23:37.560
(Sarah): Okay!

23:38.650 --> 23:43.490
-Hello? Who's this?
-Marley Corbett. Did I win?

23:43.570 --> 23:46.790
-You're caller 97! Congratulations.
-Oh, my God.

23:46.860 --> 23:49.910
-You've just won!
-What did I win?

23:49.990 --> 23:55.210
You won a free day of hang gliding
where you'll learn how to fly!

23:55.290 --> 23:59.630
(Sarah): Oh, my God. Thank you.

24:09.840 --> 24:12.810
-Hey, how you doing?
-Not too good.

24:18.270 --> 24:21.270
Yo, J. G.

24:21.360 --> 24:24.160
-Hi.
-How's it hanging?

24:25.650 --> 24:27.780
Um-- good.

24:27.860 --> 24:30.040
You here
to work on your bedside manner?

24:30.110 --> 24:33.870
-No. Checking on some test results.
-Ah. Of course.

24:33.950 --> 24:37.050
-Are you on your own?
-Why? Want to keep me company?

24:37.120 --> 24:38.710
Yeah.

24:44.960 --> 24:48.470
-How do you feel?
-To be honest, I could use a good laugh.

24:48.550 --> 24:52.100
-Want me to tell you a joke?
-I'd prefer someone funny.

24:53.140 --> 24:55.110
Alright. What? Go.

24:57.730 --> 25:02.200
Okay, um, there's this guy that...

25:02.270 --> 25:05.150
No-- It doesn't work.

25:05.230 --> 25:08.110
It doesn't work,
because you just put me on the spot.

25:08.190 --> 25:10.410
Did you hear about the medical student

25:10.490 --> 25:13.540
who interrupted the proctologist
during a lecture?

25:13.620 --> 25:16.590
He said: "Excuse me, sir, um,

25:16.660 --> 25:20.260
uh-- is that a rectal thermometer
behind your ear?"

25:20.330 --> 25:25.380
The proctologist touched behind his ear
and said: "Oh, shit!

25:25.460 --> 25:28.260
Some asshole stole my pen."

25:31.300 --> 25:33.890
You can use that one.
I've got so many more.

25:35.260 --> 25:38.520
-You know, it's okay to feel nervous.
-I'm not.

25:38.600 --> 25:40.850
Not really.

25:40.940 --> 25:43.310
-I just..
-(Nurse): Marley Corbett?

25:52.030 --> 25:54.000
-Wish me luck.
-You don't need it.

25:54.070 --> 25:56.290
-You'll do great.
-Yes!

26:07.210 --> 26:08.840
What are you doing here?

26:08.920 --> 26:11.300
Just getting caught up.

26:11.380 --> 26:13.010
It's Saturday. Go home.

26:14.050 --> 26:17.980
-You look like shit.
-Mono's only moderately contagious.

26:18.060 --> 26:20.810
-it's so nice not having you around.
-Yeah.

26:20.890 --> 26:23.490
By the way:
I licked all the water bottles.

26:27.860 --> 26:29.730
Good afternoon.

26:32.070 --> 26:35.570
-Ummm.
-Hey! Oooh.

26:35.660 --> 26:39.460
You. Hi. Wow.

26:39.540 --> 26:43.170
Yeah, my belly button is in
a different zip code than the rest of me.

26:43.250 --> 26:44.870
It just pops.

26:44.960 --> 26:47.590
-How was the appointment?
-Oh, good.

26:47.670 --> 26:52.050
My doctor says that
everything is good. Thank God.

26:54.720 --> 26:57.890
-I'm sorry.
-That's okay.

26:57.970 --> 27:01.900
'Cause I bet my doctor
is way cuter than your doctor.

27:01.970 --> 27:06.530
Marley! Please tell me
you're not flirting with your doctor.

27:06.600 --> 27:09.700
-So what if I am?
-Never mind.

27:09.770 --> 27:11.900
-Say what you're gonna say.
-No, I...

27:12.030 --> 27:15.280
Why do I feel like I'm more concerned
about this than you are?

27:15.360 --> 27:20.420
Shouldn't you focus on getting cured
rather than getting laid?

27:20.490 --> 27:22.590
Can't I do both?

27:22.660 --> 27:27.040
Could you just for once
not treat everything like it was a joke?

27:41.890 --> 27:45.110
Hey, sleepy monster,
do you want to go for a walk?

27:48.980 --> 27:50.980
You need to go for a walk.

27:55.530 --> 27:56.700
Fine.

27:58.320 --> 28:00.540
Mommy's going for a walk.

28:06.580 --> 28:11.460
♪ you never know
when time stops hanging out

28:13.170 --> 28:16.800
♪ and your friends
stop coming 'round

28:19.680 --> 28:24.150
I money comes
and money goes

28:26.100 --> 28:28.770
♪ it happens all the time

28:31.400 --> 28:36.490
♪ the sky will never give up on me

28:37.530 --> 28:43.040
♪ and the moon will always shine
at night

28:44.200 --> 28:49.460
♪ and old Mississippi River
just keeps on winding

28:50.500 --> 28:55.930
♪ it lets me know
it's gonna be alright

28:57.760 --> 29:01.480
♪ I gotta learn
to trust somebody

29:04.010 --> 29:08.060
♪ need to let someone in
Yes, I do

29:10.060 --> 29:15.240
♪ I wanna fly
but I keep falling down

29:15.320 --> 29:20.290
♪ please you all
help me get up again

29:21.860 --> 29:27.340
♪ why must I hide
behind the make-up of a fool? ♪

29:48.060 --> 29:50.360
-Hi.
-What do you think?

29:50.430 --> 29:52.480
It's good. I like it.

29:52.560 --> 29:54.980
Plus, I learned from those ladies
over there,

29:55.060 --> 29:58.280
what do you call a jazz musician
without a girlfriend?

29:58.360 --> 30:02.240
-Here we go. What?
-He doesn't have a home.

30:07.290 --> 30:09.660
It's 'homeless'.

30:09.750 --> 30:11.500
But 'A' for effort.

30:18.300 --> 30:22.850
-So that was incredible.
-He's been performing since he was 8.

30:22.930 --> 30:26.650
-Wow!
-So, what are you doing now?

30:26.720 --> 30:29.440
Want to get
something to eat with me?

30:29.520 --> 30:35.520
-Like, gefilte fish tacos, perhaps.
-No, I can't stay. I'd love to,

30:35.600 --> 30:39.650
but it's not doctor protocol
to hang around with a patient.

30:39.730 --> 30:42.160
Well, I won't say anything
if you don't.

30:45.530 --> 30:47.950
I'm really fun.

30:52.250 --> 30:54.920
How can I say no to that, right?

30:59.170 --> 31:02.220
Do you mind if I ask you
a personal question?

31:02.300 --> 31:05.220
-No.
-Why do you not have a girlfriend?

31:07.350 --> 31:11.690
-Is it that obvious?
-Oh, yeah. Yup.

31:11.770 --> 31:15.860
-I practically live at the hospital.
-Not much of a life.

31:15.940 --> 31:18.690
Actually, Dr Sanders
called me to work here

31:18.770 --> 31:23.280
out of more than 2000 applicants.
I can't sacrifice that for a personal life.

31:23.360 --> 31:25.360
Uh-uh.

31:25.450 --> 31:29.420
I guess I'm more of a
cake-and-eat-it-too kind of girl.

31:29.490 --> 31:30.580
-Oh, yeah?
-Hm.

31:30.660 --> 31:33.130
Then why aren't you
in a relationship?

31:33.200 --> 31:36.550
Because I don't need to be in one
to have a personal life.

31:36.620 --> 31:39.670
-You're not answering the question.
-Well,

31:39.750 --> 31:43.930
read about it in my next book:
'Why relationships suck ass!

31:44.010 --> 31:47.640
You know, I've never met anyone
that talks so much

31:47.720 --> 31:50.350
and says nothing at the same time.

31:51.390 --> 31:53.890
Okay. Fine.

31:55.100 --> 31:57.320
That was so...

32:03.360 --> 32:04.830
This is me.

32:09.490 --> 32:12.490
And-- that's me over there.

32:14.750 --> 32:16.710
Good night, Dr G.

32:18.080 --> 32:19.380
Good night.

32:27.550 --> 32:30.930
I'm making you
a nice, big, juicy steak.

32:31.010 --> 32:35.020
Ma! I've been a vegetarian
for 12 years.

32:35.100 --> 32:38.100
Well, you need some protein.

32:40.020 --> 32:41.490
Mm-hmm.

32:42.520 --> 32:45.030
By the way, your father called again.

32:46.530 --> 32:50.120
He said he was going to do
his best to make it out here.

32:50.200 --> 32:53.540
Blah, blah, blah.

32:53.620 --> 32:57.090
I don't know why you didn't have
your friend Sarah watch the dog.

32:57.160 --> 32:59.090
Then I could stay here with you.

32:59.170 --> 33:02.040
Strike one.
Wanna try for two?

33:02.130 --> 33:04.930
Well, I can't control my allergies.

33:05.000 --> 33:07.050
Or her complaining.

33:07.130 --> 33:09.100
I heard that.

33:11.840 --> 33:14.970
I just wanna help.
Tell me what to do.

33:15.060 --> 33:17.100
Mom, you're here. That's enough.

33:17.180 --> 33:19.610
Would you go to a nutritionist
if I could arrange it?

33:19.690 --> 33:21.610
-Mom!
-Everybody,

33:21.690 --> 33:25.910
-swears by this macrobiotic diet.
-I don't want that heely-feely shit.

33:25.980 --> 33:27.990
So just back off.

33:31.660 --> 33:34.450
Oh, this steak is burning.

33:36.700 --> 33:38.630
Go rub some dander on her.

33:38.700 --> 33:40.630
Go.

33:43.500 --> 33:47.970
Shoo! Shoo! Call him, Marley.
Call him. That's not funny.

33:49.170 --> 33:52.050
Hi, Dr Sanders. Marley.

33:53.090 --> 33:54.560
Have a seat.

33:56.600 --> 34:00.350
-Is anyone joining you? Mother?
-Trust me,

34:00.430 --> 34:02.480
neither of us wants her here.

34:04.730 --> 34:06.530
-Hi.
-Uh-oh.

34:06.610 --> 34:09.409
Two against one.
This can't be good.

34:11.070 --> 34:16.370
Marley, I'm sorry I have to say this,
but there's been no improvement.

34:17.830 --> 34:19.540
-Wait. What are you saying?

34:19.620 --> 34:22.750
The chemo hasn't worked
as we had hoped.

34:24.330 --> 34:27.260
And the tumours
have continued to grow.

34:27.340 --> 34:29.760
What now?
What...

34:29.840 --> 34:34.219
There is one particular clinical trial
that's had some success.

34:34.300 --> 34:39.020
Although, typically with patients
who had better result from chemo.

34:39.100 --> 34:42.480
Success like people cured?

34:42.560 --> 34:44.980
-Yeah.
-What is it?

34:45.060 --> 34:49.159
It's a series of treatments,
two times a week.

34:49.230 --> 34:51.239
It's injected into the affected areas.

34:51.320 --> 34:56.250
The objective is to stop or slow down
the growth of the cancerous cells.

34:56.320 --> 34:57.420
It's an option.

34:57.490 --> 35:01.750
But you need to be aware that
the side effects are very extreme.

35:01.830 --> 35:04.000
There are no guarantees.

35:08.170 --> 35:09.590
Of course.

35:11.170 --> 35:12.920
We have to do it.

35:16.220 --> 35:18.440
So you're going to be a guinea pig?

35:18.510 --> 35:21.480
It's not an experiment.
It's a clinical trial.

35:21.560 --> 35:24.690
What do you know about this trial?
What are the success rates?

35:24.770 --> 35:27.270
-He said they're pretty good.
-Pretty good?

35:27.350 --> 35:30.900
And that's it? You're going
to do it just off of that?

35:30.980 --> 35:34.860
Actually no, I flipped a coin.
Heads do it. Tails drop dead.

35:34.950 --> 35:37.920
Look, I'm just saying
that we need to make sure this is

35:37.990 --> 35:41.210
-the appropriate course of action.
-Excuse me. We?

35:41.290 --> 35:42.750
As in you, Mom and me?

35:42.830 --> 35:45.830
When have you ever been around
to make any important decision?

35:45.910 --> 35:50.010
You know what? I'm not going to have
this conversation with you. I...

36:06.940 --> 36:09.910
Will she be able to go home today?

36:09.980 --> 36:12.570
Depends on how she responds
to the treatment.

36:15.190 --> 36:16.700
Ow!

36:16.780 --> 36:19.620
Can I be here
while you do the procedure?

36:19.700 --> 36:20.820
No.

36:21.700 --> 36:23.700
I'm sorry, you cannot.

36:28.670 --> 36:31.640
What if I'm very, very quiet?

36:36.130 --> 36:40.850
Sorry, but the concept of my mother
being quiet is incredibly funny.

36:42.010 --> 36:43.690
It is.

36:46.890 --> 36:51.190
-(Marley): Am I gonna lose my hair?
-(Doctor): No, your hair will be fine.

36:53.770 --> 36:56.200
-(Marley): Ow!
-(Doctor): I'm sorry.

37:08.750 --> 37:12.590
"Roses are red, violets are blue,

37:13.710 --> 37:16.340
I've got ass cancer,

37:18.550 --> 37:20.930
now you know too."

37:21.010 --> 37:24.480
Don't you feel guilty for
leaving me all those nasty messages

37:24.560 --> 37:26.480
for missing work?

37:26.560 --> 37:28.060
Yeah, but I'm...

37:29.350 --> 37:33.570
You should have come to me sooner.
Why did you keep it a secret?

37:33.650 --> 37:37.280
Because I didn't want you
to look at me the way you are now.

37:44.740 --> 37:48.000
So, have you filed
with the insurance company?

37:48.080 --> 37:50.710
Well, I'm not footing the bill
out of my salary.

37:50.790 --> 37:52.760
No, I mean life insurance.

37:52.830 --> 37:57.130
Look, people recover from cancer
and, um,

37:57.210 --> 38:01.010
however much money you need
to make that happen, I want you to have.

38:01.090 --> 38:05.970
There's an option in the company policy
that says that anybody who has a

38:07.770 --> 38:10.390
life-threatening illness

38:10.480 --> 38:13.360
-can cash out.
-Meaning how much?

38:14.400 --> 38:15.570
A million dollars.

38:15.650 --> 38:19.280
Let me guess. That would be
500,000 dollars after taxes.

38:23.610 --> 38:26.160
I think my God will be Gucci.

38:27.620 --> 38:30.590
-Yeah, definitely.
-I think so.

38:32.120 --> 38:34.880
-Oh, I love it.
-You can fight me for it.

38:34.960 --> 38:37.800
I've got a big G for gorgeous.

38:37.880 --> 38:40.680
Cammie goes to college,
or Mommy gets this bag.

38:42.170 --> 38:43.600
(Sarah): Love you.

38:44.340 --> 38:45.390
(Peter): Okay.

38:45.470 --> 38:47.640
They're fabulous!

38:52.810 --> 38:54.530
I want you to have these.

38:59.020 --> 39:00.700
Am I making you hot?

39:02.150 --> 39:06.200
What kind of cologne is that?
He was flirting with me.

39:06.280 --> 39:08.660
-(Marley): Oh, boy.
-(Sarah): You're so weird.

39:11.750 --> 39:12.870
Hey-

39:13.910 --> 39:17.340
There's a maternity department upstairs.
Want to check that out?

39:17.420 --> 39:22.670
You know-- I'm really tired.
I'm gonna go home and lie down.

39:22.760 --> 39:26.260
Um, thank you so much for today.

39:26.340 --> 39:29.100
-I'll call you later. I love you.
-I love you too.

39:35.770 --> 39:36.820
(Sarah): I like that.

39:36.900 --> 39:39.820
(Peter): Looks like something
a stripper would wear.

39:39.900 --> 39:44.870
-Is everything okay?
-No. it's not okay.

39:44.950 --> 39:47.490
-She's really sick.
-I know.

39:47.570 --> 39:51.830
I'm trying so hard to play along,
but I'm terrible at it.

39:51.910 --> 39:56.130
And l-- I just don't want
to ruin her day.

39:56.210 --> 39:58.880
That's the last thing I want to do,
so-- bye.

40:03.630 --> 40:05.630
I'll take her home.

40:10.720 --> 40:14.150
-NO!
-It would look so nice on you.

40:14.220 --> 40:18.820
-Yes, it would. If I was you.
-A simple 'no' would have sufficed.

40:18.900 --> 40:21.450
I don't need no clothes.
This is for you guys.

40:21.520 --> 40:24.740
Everything you own
is swimming on you.

40:24.820 --> 40:29.370
-The swimming look is in.
-I just want my daughter to look good.

40:29.450 --> 40:31.790
When you look good, you feel good.

40:31.870 --> 40:35.340
I don't need a new wardrobe
to feel good.

40:35.410 --> 40:38.210
You also don't need
a negative attitude.

40:38.290 --> 40:41.540
You need to wake up and realize
I'm not getting any better.

40:41.630 --> 40:44.010
-Can we not do this here.
-No. Seriously!

40:44.090 --> 40:47.310
You always bitch about
how Dad can't confront anything

40:47.380 --> 40:49.380
and here you are
walking around in a haze,

40:49.470 --> 40:53.190
like protein and a designer dress
are going to cure my cancer.

41:00.150 --> 41:02.270
Ahhhh!

41:03.900 --> 41:06.370
This is the car. This one.
Thank you.

41:06.440 --> 41:10.200
-Was it really that bad?
-I heard you from Jimmy Choo.

41:11.490 --> 41:16.340
-it's just that she drives me crazy.
-Well, duh! She's your Mom.

41:16.410 --> 41:18.040
That's her job.

41:19.080 --> 41:21.800
-Thanks for everything.
-Thank you.

41:21.880 --> 41:25.550
Ah. OW. Ah.

41:26.590 --> 41:27.930
Marley.

41:28.970 --> 41:31.720
Hey. it's okay.

41:33.430 --> 41:35.600
Just give me a second.

41:36.970 --> 41:39.150
It's gonna be okay.

41:45.690 --> 41:48.410
-Is she gonna be alright?
-She's dehydrated.

41:48.490 --> 41:51.110
A couple of bags of saline
and she'll be feeling better.

41:51.200 --> 41:52.700
She is right here, people.

41:52.780 --> 41:55.200
'Shop till you drop'
is only an expression.

41:55.280 --> 41:56.910
Not bad.

41:56.990 --> 41:59.620
That's the best thing
I could come up with.

41:59.710 --> 42:01.300
Dr G.

42:01.370 --> 42:03.670
-Ah, hi.
-Hi. Hello.

42:03.750 --> 42:06.970
GI extra ordinaire.
Artist extra ordinaire.

42:07.050 --> 42:09.140
-Pleased to meet you.
-Nice to-- oh!

42:09.210 --> 42:10.260
I...

42:11.430 --> 42:14.850
I'm suddenly in the mood for some Jell-O.
Do you need anything?

42:14.930 --> 42:16.650
Really? Jell-O?

42:18.600 --> 42:21.150
-I'm good. Thanks.
-Okay.

42:22.940 --> 42:27.610
Strangely, she's not so good
with needles. Ouch!

42:27.690 --> 42:31.490
-So what happened?
-I don't know. I just had a

42:31.570 --> 42:35.120
-sudden, searing pain.
-Hm.

42:35.200 --> 42:37.040
Come on, doc. Level with me.

42:38.120 --> 42:40.090
Is all this really
gonna be worth it?

42:40.160 --> 42:42.920
Yeah, um-- well just

42:43.000 --> 42:45.970
-tell me where exactly...
-OW!

42:46.040 --> 42:47.220
Sorry.

42:49.050 --> 42:53.050
Well, there was a pain in my ass,
but then I realized it was my mother.

42:53.130 --> 42:56.180
Marley, come on.
Just answer the question.

42:56.260 --> 43:00.230
Is there a woman with a very big needle
standing next to me?

43:01.270 --> 43:05.270
Ow! That's my skin
you're pricking.

43:05.350 --> 43:07.610
I'm sorry. I can't seem
to find a vein.

43:07.690 --> 43:09.160
Let me try.

43:22.450 --> 43:24.210
Dr G?

43:25.540 --> 43:27.790
I think I found one.

43:34.590 --> 43:37.060
I don't know how it's doing
against my cancer,

43:37.140 --> 43:40.440
but this treatment
sure is kicking my ass.

43:40.510 --> 43:42.520
Two down, eight to go.

43:42.600 --> 43:45.320
Hey, Marley. Hey. Marley.

43:45.390 --> 43:47.820
